This paper deals with the analysis of crypto-mining malware, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses both static and dynamic analysis techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and distributed computing (cs.DC) research. The paper also discusses the infrastructure and underground economies supporting the malware, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
